file.name: netwitness_suite.yaml
file.content:
components:
  schemas:
    tmp0:
      properties:
        attachment: {type: string}
        logs: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp1:
      properties:
        attachment: {type: string}
        logs: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp2:
      properties:
        attachment: {type: string}
        logs: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp3:
      properties:
        meta: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp4:
      properties:
        meta: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp5:
      properties:
        meta: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp6:
      properties:
        attachment: {type: string}
        pcap: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp7:
      properties:
        attachment: {type: string}
        pcap: {type: string}
      type: object
    tmp8:
      properties:
        attachment: {type: string}
        pcap: {type: string}
      type: object
  securitySchemes:
    BasicAuth: {scheme: basic, type: http}
info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of RSA NetWitness Suite
  title: RSA NetWitness Suite
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Retrieve logs involving provided IP address(es)
      parameters:
      - description: Comma or newline separated list of IP addresses to search for
          in sessions
        example: 8.8.8.8, 8.8.4.4
        in: query
        name: IP Address(es)
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Minutes into the past you want to search
        example: ''
        in: body
        name: Timeframe
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get Logs by IP
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Retrieve logs using advanced query
      parameters:
      - description: Query filter using SA advanced query syntax
        example: ip.dst = 8.8.8.8 || ip.dst = 8.8.4.4
        in: query
        name: Query
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Minutes into the past you want to search
        example: ''
        in: body
        name: Timeframe
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get Logs by Query
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Retrieve logs for provided session ID(s)
      parameters:
      - description: Comma or newline separated list of session ID(s)
        example: '12345'
        in: query
        name: Session ID(s)
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get Logs by Session ID
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Retrieve session metadata for sessions involving provided IP address(es)
      parameters:
      - description: Comma or newline separated list of IP addresses to search for
          in sessions
        example: 8.8.8.8, 8.8.4.4
        in: query
        name: IP Address(es)
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Minutes into the past you want to search
        example: ''
        in: body
        name: Timeframe
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get Session Meta by IP
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Retrieve session metadata using advanced query
      parameters:
      - description: Query filter using SA advanced query syntax
        example: ip.dst = 8.8.8.8 || ip.dst = 8.8.4.4
        in: query
        name: Query
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Minutes into the past you want to search
        example: '60'
        in: body
        name: Timeframe
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get Session Meta by Query
  tmp5:
    post:
      description: Search for and retrieve session metadata for provided session ID(s)
      parameters:
      - description: Comma or newline separated list of session ID(s)
        example: '12345'
        in: query
        name: Session ID(s)
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp5'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get Session Meta by Session ID
  tmp6:
    post:
      description: Retrieve PCAP for sessions involving provided IP address(es)
      parameters:
      - description: Comma or newline separated list of IP addresses to search for
          in sessions
        example: 8.8.8.8, 8.8.4.4
        in: query
        name: IP Address(es)
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Minutes into the past you want to search
        example: ''
        in: body
        name: Timeframe
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp6'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get PCAP by IP
  tmp7:
    post:
      description: Retrieve PCAP for sessions involving provided IP address(es)
      parameters:
      - description: Query filter using SA advanced query syntax
        example: ip.dst = 8.8.8.8 || ip.dst = 8.8.4.4
        in: query
        name: Query
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Minutes into the past you want to search
        example: ''
        in: body
        name: Timeframe
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp7'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get PCAP by Query
  tmp8:
    post:
      description: Retrieve PCAP for provided session ID(s)
      parameters:
      - description: Comma or newline separated list of session ID(s)
        example: '12345'
        in: query
        name: Session ID(s)
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp8'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: Get PCAP by Session ID
tags:
- {name: SIEM & Log Management}
